title: For Sale/Trade:  Grendel P12 - compact .380 auto 12 shot
postcontent: Up for sale is a NIB never fired Grendel P12. I bought this years ago, oiled it up, put it away and simply forgot about it. For those who may be interested - Grendel was a hot manufacturer of mostly high capacity weapons in the early 90's. Then came the first assault weapon ban and Grendel silently faded away. However they were resurrected four or five years later as KelTec... same owner, same Florida location. Today KelTec is the third largest manufacturer of handguns in the USA. So if this Grendel resembles a KelTec you've seen that is why. Bottom line is this is a lot of firepower in a very small package. The .380 cartridge is no slouch and many feel that it's about top of the line for a truly concealable pistol. This P12 is much smaller than the compact 9mm's or .40's I've seen. Gun comes in factory plastic case with manual and a spare magazine (mag holds 11 with one in the chamber). Design of this pistol allows it to be carried safely with a chambered round.
